		<part>
			<title>API Business Value</title>
			<slide id="api101">
				<title>API 101</title>
				<img src="api-value-101.png" style=" width : 90% ; height : 70% ; object-fit : contain ; margin : 0% 4% 0% 4% ; "/>
			</slide>
			<slide id="api-integration">
				<title>APIs and Integration</title>
				<ul>
					<li>Are APIs just another name for integration?</li>
					<ul>
						<li><em>Integration</em> is 1:1 and requires bilateral effort every single time</li>
						<li><em>Interconnection</em> is n:m and is designed to easily scale up</li>
					</ul>
					<li><q>APIs are just integration</q> is a good litmus test for API effectivity</li>
					<ul>
						<li>If it is true → APIs could be used more effectively</li>
						<li>Existing integrations are a great starting point for <em>API archaeology</em></li>
						<li><a href="http://dret.net/lectures/api-days-finland-2019/" title='Erik Wilde, "Enjoy Responsibly: Minimizing Coupling for API Consumption", API Days Finland 2019, Helsinki, Finland, 6/5/2019'>Loose coupling</a> is one of the critical API properties</li>
					</ul>
				</ul>
			</slide>
			<slide id="api-consumers">
				<title>Many API Consumers</title>
				<img src="api-value-many-consumers.png" style=" width : 90% ; height : 70% ; object-fit : contain ; margin : 0% 4% 0% 4% ; "/>
			</slide>
			<slide id="consuming-apis">
				<title>Consuming Many APIs</title>
				<img src="api-value-many-consuming.png" style=" width : 90% ; height : 70% ; object-fit : contain ; margin : 0% 4% 0% 4% ; "/>
			</slide>
			<slide id="api-complexity">
				<title>API Complexity</title>
				<img src="api-value-complexity.png" style=" width : 90% ; height : 70% ; object-fit : contain ; margin : 0% 4% 0% 4% ; "/>
			</slide>
			<slide id="duality">
				<title>API Value Duality</title>
				<ul>
					<li><em>Partners/Public API use</em> enables API economy participation</li>
					<ul>
						<li><em>Exposing APIs</em> expands the footprint of available products</li>
						<li><em>Using APIs</em> allows building value chains across organizations</li>
						<li>The business can expose a platform to the outside</li>
					</ul>
					<li><em>Private APIs</em> fulfill the goal of business-level agility</li>
					<ul>
						<li>Every capability is designed and built to be used individually</li>
						<li>Managing APIs becomes synonymous with managing business capabilities</li>
						<li>Business itself becomes platform-driven</li>
					</ul>
				</ul>
			</slide>
			<slide id="api-challenges">
				<title>API Challenges</title>
				<ul>
					<li>Challenges from the business perspective</li>
					<ul>
						<li>Balance risk/cost and necessary investments in business agility</li>
						<li>Start making <q>API thinking (i.e., agility) part of business culture</q></li>
					</ul>
					<li>Challenges from the team perspective</li>
					<ul>
						<li>Enable and empower teams by reducing command-and-control structures</li>
						<li>Start building feedback structures for observing/supporting teams</li>
					</ul>
					<li>Challenges from the technology perspective</li>
					<ul>
						<li>Enable and empower developers to adjust to the ecosystem approach</li>
						<li>Move architecture from "how" to "what" and practice loose coupling</li>
					</ul>
				</ul>
			</slide>
